{"book":"2 Corinthians","chapter":2,"questions":[{"id":"2cor-2-q1","type":"multiple_choice","question":"What does Paul urge the Corinthians to do for the person who caused grief?","options":["Punish him more severely","Forgive and comfort him","Send him away","Ignore him"],"answer":"Forgive and comfort him","verse_reference":"2 Corinthians 2:7"},{"id":"2cor-2-q2","type":"multiple_choice","question":"Paul describes believers as what kind of fragrance to God?","options":["The aroma of Christ","The scent of myrrh","The smell of incense","The fragrance of roses"],"answer":"The aroma of Christ","verse_reference":"2 Corinthians 2:15"},{"id":"2cor-2-q3","type":"true_false","question":"Paul says unforgiveness can be a scheme of Satan to take advantage of believers.","answer":"true","verse_reference":"2 Corinthians 2:10-11"},{"id":"2cor-2-q4","type":"fill_blank","question":"We are not unaware of Satan's _____.","answer":"schemes","verse_reference":"2 Corinthians 2:11"},{"id":"2cor-2-q5","type":"fill_blank","question":"Thanks be to God, who always leads us in _____ in Christ.","answer":"triumph","verse_reference":"2 Corinthians 2:14"}]}
